      "name": "CFD hemolysis index validation against in-vitro measurements — FDA pump geometry",
      "description": "Steady-state RANS simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump at five operating points. Hemolysis index computed via power-law damage accumulation model. Validation performed against in-vitro NIH measurements at matched flow rates. RH values at all five operating points fall below 1.0, supporting acceptance of the worst-case identification claim.",
      "validationMethod": "Quantitative comparison of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) between CFD predictions and experimental measurements at five flow-speed combinations spanning the clinical operating envelope."
